INSERT INTO `wp_comments` VALUES (50, 87, '78mgb (Matt Barcomb)', '', '', '', '2010-02-26 02:43:28', '2010-02-26 02:43:28', '&lt;span&gt;Great post Abby!  In most blog posts I usually find some point of contention or gap or desire more clarity.  This had none of those; it was clear and concise.  You did a good job of pointing out some common misconceptions of &quot;doing agile&quot; and I really liked the tie-in to lean as the foundation behind the agile principles.  I&#39;ve recently been trying to introduce lean principles myself and ran into a wall with folks not wanting to &quot;switch agile practices&quot;.  I plan on using this blog to articulate that it&#39;s not switching at all, but really what we *should* have been focusing on all along :)&lt;/span&gt;<br /><br />Cheers,<br />-Matt', 0, '1', '', '', 0, 0);
