INSERT INTO `wp_comments` VALUES (54, 87, 'The Abbot of Unreason', '', '', '', '2010-02-26 18:43:10', '2010-02-26 18:43:10', 'Oh, man, logging in <i>after</i> typing in my comment erases the comment!<br /><br />And it was a brilliant comment, I assure you :)<br /><br />At any rate, I really liked this bit:  &quot;&lt;span&gt;Because software is a knowledge-creating process, the more we build, the more we know.&quot;  (I mean, I liked the whole thing, of course.  But this stood out.)  It reminded me that the more we write down the more we <i>think</i> we know.  And we have to carry all that requirement knowledge on our shoulders (or in our backpacks a la Up in the Air) like a ton of stones.  It takes up space that we could better devote to understanding the individual stones.  And it slows us down.  And these stones are weighing us down until we get around to actually pulling one off, shaping it to our needs, and putting it into the wall of software.  Or something.&lt;/span&gt;<br /><br />Another great post.', 0, '1', '', '', 0, 0);
